Project Context

This is a Pokémon TCG ecommerce and inventory management system called "TCG".
Tech stack: Next.js 14 (App Router), Payload CMS 3, Supabase (PostgreSQL), Tailwind CSS, TypeScript.
The full build plan is in `docs/build-plan.md` — always refer to it to understand what phase we are in and what comes next.
The full database schema is in `docs/database.md` — always refer to it when creating or modifying any Payload collection.

Coding Rules

Always use TypeScript — never use plain JavaScript
Always use the App Router — never use the Pages Router
Never use any as a TypeScript type — use proper types or unknown
Always use Tailwind CSS for styling — never write custom CSS unless absolutely unavoidable
Always use Payload's local API for server-side data fetching — never call the REST API from the server
Use the REST API only for client-side fetching where the local API is not available
Never hardcode strings like currency, store name, or URLs — use environment variables or Site Settings
All price values are in GBP (£) unless explicitly stated otherwise

Payload CMS Rules

Every collection must match the schema defined in `docs/database.md` exactly — do not add or remove fields without being told to
Always add admin labels and descriptions to collection fields so the admin panel is easy to use
Always group related fields using Payload's group or tabs field types where it improves readability
Always add access controls to every collection — default to admin-only unless told otherwise
Never use Payload's versions or drafts features unless explicitly asked
Always add timestamps: true to every collection

File Structure Rules

All Payload collections go in `/collections/`
All Payload globals go in `/globals/`
All Next.js app routes go in `/app/(app)/`
All reusable React components go in `/components/`
All utility/helper functions go in `/lib/`
All TypeScript types go in `/types/`
Seed scripts go in `/scripts/`

Behaviour Rules

Always read `docs/build-plan.md` and `docs/database.md` before starting any task
Only build what is asked for in the current phase — do not jump ahead or add features not in the current phase
If something in the request conflicts with `docs/database.md` or `docs/build-plan.md`, flag it before writing any code
Always explain what you are doing and why in plain English before writing code — this project is being built by a beginner who is learning
When creating a new file, always state the file path at the top of your response
If a task requires running a terminal command, show it clearly and tell me to run it before continuing
Never delete or overwrite existing files without explicitly warning me first
If you are unsure about anything, ask a clarifying question rather than guessing

After creating the file, confirm it has been created and give me a one-line summary of what each section does.

